&\overset{3|10}{=} 3^{a_3} \cdot 5^b \cdot 7^c \cdot 2^d \cdot 1^e\\
\text{Since } 3 \mid 10 \implies a_3 \geq 1,\\
a_3 &= \left[\frac{10}{3}\right] + \left[\frac{4}{3}\right] + \left[\frac{2}{3}\right] \\
&= 3 + 1 + 0 = \boxed{4}.
\end{aligned}
$$
Therefore, $x^3$ is a factor of $10!$ exactly 4 times, so there are $\boxed{4}$ possible integer values of $x$. The answer is: 4.
